President Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated former National Chairman of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, on his 70th birthday.  In a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Mr Femi Adesina, Buhari commended the leadership capacities of the man who, before taking charge as Edo Governor for eight years, served as President of the Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC) “President Muhammadu Buhari joins leaders and members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in celebrating with former Governor of Edo State, Comrade Adams Aliyu Oshiomhole, on his 70th birthday, April 4, 2022.   BREAKING (Grammys 2022) : Wizkid, Femi Kuti, son lose to…     M.I Abaga announces engagement to Eniola Mafe     BREAKING: Gunmen kill three FRSC officials in Anambra   “The President congratulates the former Chairman of the APC on another milestone, saluting his salutary contributions to development of democracy and good governance. “President Buhari believes Comrade Oshiomhole’s leadership strides in various sectors will stand the test of time, deploying his time and strength to the good of workers and Nigerians as a labour leader, Chairman of the Nigerian Labour Congress, and accepting the call into politics to serve his state. “The President notes the mental soundness and experience of the former APC leader, willingly dedicating himself for the greater good of the country, and acting as the voice of the voiceless in different ramifications. “As the former Governor turns 70, the President prays for good health, and continued service to God and humanity,” the statement reads.